My company recently worked with the Hilton to host a multi-day conference for over 100 of our summer interns. This is the second time we've held the event here and I have to say I am very pleased with the hotel in general.  No, this is not the fanciest or newest hotel. You can certainly see the age. However, it is centrally located, the staff is very polite, and the hotel is clean. We arranged a pre-con meeting with the hotel and they brought in about 10 department heads to meet with our team. They were very respectful and made us feel valued.  We reserved the majority of the meeting rooms and held buffet meals in the ballrooms. All of the setups were on time and the meals were delicious. Most of our interns stayed at the hotel as well. The hotel staff was always available to accommodate any of our requests.  I was in a corner room with an excellent view on the 21st floor and had access to the executive lounge on the 22nd floor. We ate breakfast in the lounge a few times and the only thing is I wish they would allow me to heat up pastries (croissants taste much better warm).

